FT  16 OCT 92 / The Birmingham Summit: Heath pours scorn on subsidiarity
debate
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SHEILA JONES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EUROPEAN COMMUNITY leaders should be planning a way out of recession rather
than discussing the minute detail of EC decision-making, Mr Edward Heath,
former Conservative prime minister, said yesterday.
'For the top brass to spend a day arguing about the minutiae of subsidiarity
during an international economic crisis of this severity is ludicrous. We
joined the Community to do as much as possible together. Never was it more
needed than today,' Mr Heath said. He was speaking at the 20th anniversary
gathering in London of the Franco-British Council.
Mr Heath said the lesson of the ERM crisis was the need for a single
currency.
'If we are not to have our currencies picked off one by one by speculators
we must have the strength of one single currency to resist and destroy
them,' he said.
