FT  16 OCT 92 / German immigration vote fails
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Opposition Social Democrats in the German parliament remain in their seats,
boycotting a vote yesterday on changing the constitution to stop the flood
of foreign refugees, Reuter reports from Bonn. As a result, Chancellor
Helmut Kohl was denied the necessary two-thirds majority and the motion
failed. The SPD had wanted the debate postponed until after it holds a
special party congress on the issue next month.
