</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The rising gas price has helped Richmond Oil &amp; Gas, loss-making natural
resources company, forge a joint venture to revive Texas properties.
The group said yesterday that two US energy companies had agreed to invest
Dollars 2.2m in developing Richmond's Panhandle, Texas, operations, Richmond
receiving a 30 per cent working interest through completion in 20 new wells.
Earlier this year, the SFO launched an inquiry into aspects surrounding
Richmond's 1989 flotation.
