FT  15 OCT 92 / International Company News: CBS returns to the black with
Dollars 42.7m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CBS, the US broadcasting group which owns one of the country's leading
television networks, yesterday reported third-quarter net profits of Dollars
42.7m, a significant recovery when compared with a loss of Dollars 169.1m
suffered in the same period of last year.
The profit, struck on revenues 7.5 per cent up at Dollars 672.8m, translates
into earnings per share of Dollars 2.76, against a loss of Dollars 11.11 per
share a year ago.
CBS said its third-quarter earnings a year ago included a Dollars 195.5m
provision related to broadcasts of professional baseball and football.
The company, which is controlled by Mr Larry Tisch, the billionaire
investor, said profits also benefited from the combined effect of a stronger
prime-time programme schedule, better advertisement pricing and active cost
control.
The CBS television network returned to a 'slightly profitable level' in the
third quarter. Net interest income of Dollars 21.5m also helped, as it was
twice the level of a year ago. Interest income on investments in the quarter
included capital gains of Dollars 14.5m.
For the first nine months of 1992, CBS had net income of Dollars 53.8m,
compared with a loss of Dollars 95.2m in the same period of 1991. Revenues
were Dollars 2.53bn in the first nine months of this year, compared with
Dollars 2.09bn last year.
On Wall Street, the CBS share price was marked Dollars 1 1/4 lower at
Dollars 206.
</TEXT>
