<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 92 / The ERM and Maastricht: Franc emerges 'intact and
reinforced'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BUCHAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The franc has emerged 'intact and reinforced' from last month's monetary
crisis, Mr Jacques De Larosiere, the Banque of France governor, said
yesterday, writes David Buchan in Paris. Almost half of the FFr160bn (Pounds
18.7bn) spent in supporting the franc's parity against the D-Mark was
flowing back, as speculators gambling on the franc's devaluation had to buy
it back at an unchanged rate, he said.
The governor gave no details of last month's intervention, but it is
believed that half came from French reserves and the remainder from the
Bundesbank. He said Germans had done all they could to help the pound and
the lira.
