FT  15 OCT 92 / MI6 link with toolmaker alleged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A FORMER executive with Matrix Churchill, the Coventry-based machine tool
makers, was working for MI6, the secret intelligence service while promoting
the company's exports, the Old Bailey heard.
Mr Mark Gutteridge, a former export sales manager with the Iraqi-owned
company, worked for MI6 with the approval of Mr Paul Henderson, the
company's managing director, Mr Geoffrey Robertson QC, for Mr Henderson,
told the court.
He was cross-examining Mr Ronald Ash, a former defence project executive
with Matrix Churchill who worked with Mr Gutteridge in building the
company's trading links with Iraq.
Mr Henderson, Mr Trevor Abraham, a former commercial director with the
company and Mr Peter Allen, a former sales director, all deny breaking
export regulations to sell Iraq machine tools with a military application.
The trial continues today.
