FT  15 OCT 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Wool prices in terms of Australian cents have been edging slightly lower at
sales this week. The change in the Wool Corporation's market indicator is
small, down 5 cents to 527c/kg on October 14. This is, however, a new low
for the season, and fractional though the change may be, the tendency is not
helpful to the trade. The recession is frequently mentioned as a factor
throughout the world, with Europe as depressed as the UK itself. Currency
volatility and uncartainty holds back buying confidence at every stage, and
there are no signs of an about-turn.
