FT  15 OCT 92 / Maternity seen as career handicap
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DIANE SUMMERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MANY WOMEN with prof-essional or managerial jobs feel their career prospects
are damaged after taking a break to have a baby, Diane Summers writes.
The finding comes in a survey of nearly 800 women published today by Sussex
University on behalf of employers including Marks and Spencer and Barclays
Bank.
Before taking a career break, 84 per cent of women were very satisfied or
satisfied with the way they were promoted at work. After returning to work,
that dropped to 64 per cent.
