<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 92 / Business pays more for lawyers in UK
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT RICE, Legal Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE UK's top commercial lawyers are the most expensive in the world,
charging Dollars 235 an hour more than their counterparts in the US,
according to an annual survey of international law firms in the
International Financial Law Review 1000. Figures show that the average
hourly rate for legal advice from a partner in a top City of London law firm
rose 20 per cent over the past 12 months to Dollars 585 an hour.
The top rate for a partner in the most expensive Wall Street firms is
Dollars 350 an hour and average hourly rates for partners in US firms are
Dollars 230.
After the UK, Germany has the most expensive law firms, with top commercial
lawyers charging Dollars 510 an hour, followed by Switzerland (Dollars 445),
Austria (Dollars 385), Japan (Dollars 350) and Hong Kong (Dollars 325).
The figures were dismissed yesterday by City lawyers as misleading. Mr Adam
Quarry of City-based solicitors Linklaters &amp; Paines said the survey was 'not
comparing like with like' and was 'a gross oversimplification' of billing
practices.
Rates quoted were partner rates whereas the true cost to a client of using
the firm's services would be a blended average of the hourly rates of the
different grades of lawyers who worked on it, he said.
</TEXT>
