<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 92 / New Kuwait cabinet
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Middle East Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
KUWAIT's new cabinet will include six elected members of the National
Assembly - the most elected members ever represented in a Kuwaiti cabinet -
under a plan agreed by the crown prince and parliamentary deputies, the
official Kuwait News Agency (KUNA) reported yesterday, our Middle East Staff
writes.
The award of six cabinet seats to deputies follows the election of an
opposition majority in the October 5 elections, the first full poll since
the last parliament was suspended in 1986.
The ministries to be taken up by the six were not known. Announcement of the
full cabinet is expected by the weekend.
