FT  15 OCT 92 / Chelsea's rare run scores Pounds 22,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CHRISTIE'S in Glasgow yesterday sold a run of rare Chelsea Football Club
programmes for Pounds 22,000, double the estimate.
The programmes were sold by Mr David Mears, a descendant of the club's
founder.
Such a complete run of programmes, gathered into 69 bound volumes, is
unprecedented. Programmes dating from before 1914 are very rare and the
collection included more than 400 of them, plus more than 1,000 pre-1939
programmes. The successful telephone bidder intends to keep the collection
intact.
The auction did very well, topping Pounds 167,000.
