<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 92 / International Capital Markets: Repurchase facility set up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LEHMAN Brothers International and Euroclear, the Brussels-based clearing
house, have set up a tri-party repurchase facility aimed at encouraging
banks and fund managers to enter the growing European repo market, writes
Tracy Corrigan.
Last month, the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD),
Swiss Bank Corporation and Cedel announced the first tri-party repurchase
agreement (repo) programme to be launched in Europe.
The repo market allows institutions to boost returns by lending out
securities on a short term basis. Tri-party programmes reduce the risk of
failed trades and lower costs for counterparties deterred by complex
processing involved in repurchase agreements.
